#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL Startup Guide"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "This document helps a user set up and use MySQL.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting Started With MySQL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"MySQL is a popular database server that is used in various applications. SQL\n"
"stands for (S)tructured (Q)uery (L)anguage, which is what MySQL uses to\n"
"communicate with other programs. On top of that, MySQL has its own expanded SQL\n"
"functions to provide additional functionality to users. In this document, we'll\n"
"look at how to do the initial MySQL installation, set up databases and tables,\n"
"and create new users. Let's start out with the installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First make sure you have MySQL installed on your system. In case you need\n"
"specific functionality from MySQL, please make sure you have the required USE\n"
"flags enabled as they will help fine tune your installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing MySQL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:57
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(View available USE flags)</comment>\n"
"# <i>emerge --pretend --verbose mysql</i>\n"
"<comment>(Install MySQL)</comment>\n"
"# <i>emerge mysql</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "Upon completion of the installation, you will see the following notice:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL einfo message"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You might want to run:\n"
"\"emerge --config =dev-db/mysql-[version]\"\n"
"if this is a new install.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Since this is a new installation, we run the command. You need to press\n"
"<c>ENTER</c> when prompted while configuring the MySQL database. The\n"
"configuration sets up the main MySQL database which contains administrative\n"
"information such as databases, tables, users, permissions and more. The\n"
"configuration recommends that you change your root password as soon as\n"
"possible. We will definitely do this, otherwise someone could come along by\n"
"chance and hack our default setup MySQL server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Replace [version] with the version number you have just installed.)</comment>\n"
"# <i>emerge --config =dev-db/mysql-[version]</i>\n"
" * MySQL DATADIR is /var/lib/mysql\n"
" * Press ENTER to create the mysql database and set proper\n"
" * permissions on it, or Control-C to abort now...\n"
"\n"
"   Preparing db table\n"
"   Preparing host table\n"
"   Preparing user table\n"
"   Preparing func table\n"
"   Preparing tables_priv table\n"
"   Preparing columns_priv table\n"
"   Installing all prepared tables\n"
"\n"
"   To start mysqld at boot time you have to copy support-files/mysql.server\n"
"   to the right place for your system\n"
"\n"
"   PLEASE REMEMBER TO SET A PASSWORD FOR THE MySQL root USER !\n"
"   To do so, issue the following commands to start the server\n"
"   and change the applicable passwords:\n"
"<comment>(Note the next 3 lines)</comment>\n"
"   /etc/init.d/mysql start\n"
"   /usr/bin/mysqladmin -u root -h pegasos password 'new-password'\n"
"   /usr/bin/mysqladmin -u root password 'new-password'\n"
"   Depending on your configuration, a -p option may be needed\n"
"   in the last command. See the manual for more details.\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Some MySQL non-ebuild specific information has been removed from here\n"
"so as to keep this document as consistent as possible)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"   * For security reasons you should set your MySQL root\n"
"   * password as soon as possible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:119
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As of mysql-4.0.24-r2, passwords are entered during the config phase making\n"
"root password entry more secure.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The config script has already printed out the commands we need to run to setup\n"
"our password, so we shall now run them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up your MySQL root password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>/etc/init.d/mysql start</i>\n"
" * Re-caching dependency info (mtimes differ)...\n"
" * Starting mysqld (/etc/mysql/my.cnf) ...        [ ok ]\n"
"<comment>(Replace new-password with your desired password)</comment>\n"
"# <i>/usr/bin/mysqladmin -u root -h localhost password 'new-password'</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:137
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can now test that your root password was successfully configured by trying\n"
"to login to your MySQL server:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "Logging into the MySQL server using mysql"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:142
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>mysql -u root -h localhost -p</i>\n"
"Enter password:\n"
"Welcome to the MySQL monitor. Commands end with ; or \\g.\n"
"Your MySQL connection id is 4 to server version: 4.0.25\n"
"\n"
"Type 'help;' or '\\h' for help. Type '\\c' to clear the buffer.\n"
"\n"
"mysql&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>-u</c> switch sets the user that will be logging in. The <c>-h</c>\n"
"switch sets the host. This will usually be <c>localhost</c> unless you are\n"
"setting up a remote server. Finally, <c>-p</c> tells the mysql client that you\n"
"will be entering a password to access your database. Notice the\n"
"<c>mysql&gt;</c> prompt. This is where you type in all your commands. Now that\n"
"we're in the mysql prompt as the root user, we can begin to setup our database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up The Database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating A Database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:172
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We have logged in and a mysql prompt is displayed. First let's take a look at\n"
"the databases we currently have. To do so, we use the <c>SHOW DATABASES</c>\n"
"command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "Displaying MySQL databases"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SHOW DATABASES;</i>\n"
"+----------+\n"
"| Database |\n"
"+----------+\n"
"| mysql    |\n"
"| test     |\n"
"+----------+\n"
"2 rows in set (0.09 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please remember that MySQL commands should end with a semicolon -- <c>;</c>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Despite the fact that a test database is already created, we are going to\n"
"create our own. Databases are created using the <c>CREATE DATABASE</c> command.\n"
"We'll create one named \"gentoo\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the gentoo database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>CREATE DATABASE gentoo;</i>\n"
"Query OK, 1 row affected (0.08 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:204
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The response lets us know that the command was executed without any errors. In\n"
"this case, 1 row was modified. This is a reference to the main mysql database,\n"
"which carries a list of all the databases. You won't need to worry too much\n"
"about the background details. The last number is how fast the query was\n"
"executed. We can verify the database was created by running the <c>SHOW\n"
"DATABASES</c> command again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:212
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifing the database is created"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SHOW DATABASES;</i>\n"
"+----------+\n"
"| Database |\n"
"+----------+\n"
"| gentoo   |\n"
"| mysql    |\n"
"| test     |\n"
"+----------+\n"
"3 rows in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Indeed our database has been created. In order to work with creating tables for\n"
"our new gentoo database, we need to select it as our current database. To do\n"
"so, we use the <c>USE</c> command. The <c>USE</c> command takes the name of the\n"
"database you wish to use as your current database. Another option is to set it\n"
"on the command line after the <c>-D</c> switch. Let's go ahead and switch to\n"
"the gentoo database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switching our database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>USE gentoo;</i>\n"
"Database changed\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"And the current database is now our previously created gentoo database. Now\n"
"that we're using it, we can start to create some tables and put information in\n"
"them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:249
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working With Tables In MySQL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a Table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the structure of MySQL, there are databases, tables, records, and fields.\n"
"Databases hold together tables, tables hold together records, records hold\n"
"together fields, which contain the actual information. This structure lets\n"
"users select how they want to access their information. So far we've dealt with\n"
"databases, now let's work with tables. First off, tables can be listed\n"
"similiarly to databases using the <c>SHOW TABLES</c> command. Right now there\n"
"are no tables in our gentoo database, as running the command will show us:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:264
#, no-wrap
msgid "Empty gentoo Database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:265
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SHOW TABLES;</i>\n"
"Empty set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This means we need to create some tables. In order to do so, we use the\n"
"<c>CREATE TABLE</c> command. However, this command is quite different from\n"
"simple <c>CREATE DATABASE</c> command. This command takes a list of arguments.\n"
"The form is as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "CREATE TABLE Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "CREATE TABLE [table_name] ([field_name] [field_data_type]([size]));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>table_name</b> is the name of the table we wish to create. In this case,\n"
"let's make a table named <c>developers</c>. This table will contain the\n"
"developer's name, email and job. <b>field_name</b> will contain the name of the\n"
"field. We have 3 required names in this case: name, email, and job. The\n"
"<b>field_data_type</b> is what type of information will be stored. The\n"
"different formats available can be found at the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/column-types.html\">MySQL Column Types\n"
"Page</uri>. For our purposes, we'll use the <c>VARCHAR</c> data type for all of\n"
"our fields. <c>VARCHAR</c> is one of the simplest of data types when it comes\n"
"to working with strings. <b>size</b> is how much of data a single field will\n"
"store. In this case, we'll use 128. This means that the field can have\n"
"<c>VARCHAR</c> data that is 128 bytes. You can safely think of this as 128\n"
"characters for the time being, though there is a somewhat more technical\n"
"explanation that the above site will provide you with. Now that we know how we\n"
"are going to create the table, let's do it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:298
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating our table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:299
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>CREATE TABLE developers ( name VARCHAR(128), email VARCHAR(128), job VARCHAR(128));</i>\n"
"Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.11 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:304
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Looks like our table was created ok. Let's check it with the <c>SHOW TABLES</c>\n"
"command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying our table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SHOW TABLES;</i>\n"
"+------------------+\n"
"| Tables_in_gentoo |\n"
"+------------------+\n"
"| developers       |\n"
"+------------------+\n"
"1 row in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:319
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Yes, there's our table. However, it doesn't seem to have any information on the\n"
"types of fields we setup. For that, we use the <c>DESCRIBE</c> command (or\n"
"<c>DESC</c> for short), which takes the name of the table as its argument.\n"
"Let's see what that gives us for our developers table.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "Describing our developers table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:326
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>DESCRIBE developers;</i>\n"
"+-------+--------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\n"
"| Field | Type         | Null | Key | Default | Extra |\n"
"+-------+--------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\n"
"| name  | varchar(128) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |\n"
"| email | varchar(128) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |\n"
"| job   | varchar(128) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |\n"
"+-------+--------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\n"
"3 rows in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:338
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This shows the different fields and their types. It also shows a few extra\n"
"attributes that are beyond the scope of this howto. Feel free to refer to the\n"
"<uri link=\"http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/\">MySQL Reference Manual</uri> for\n"
"more information. We now have a table to work with. Now let's go ahead and\n"
"populate it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid "Populating Our MySQL Database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:352
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We populate a table (or add data) using the <c>INSERT</c> command. Like the\n"
"<c>CREATE TABLE</c> command, it also has a specific format:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:356
#, no-wrap
msgid "INSERT Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:357
#, no-wrap
msgid "INSERT INTO table (col1, col2, ...) VALUES('value1', 'value2', ...);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:361
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This command is used to insert a record into table. table contains the MySQL\n"
"table we wish to enter the information into. The table name may be followed by\n"
"the list of columns to insert data into and <c>VALUES()</c> contains the values\n"
"you wish to insert into the table. You may omit the list of columns if you\n"
"insert a value into each one and if you write the values in the same order the\n"
"columns have been defined. In this case, we want to insert data into the\n"
"developers table. Let's insert sample records:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "Inserting information into our developers table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>INSERT INTO developers VALUES('Joe Smith', 'joesmith@gentoo.org', 'toolchain');</i>\n"
"Query OK, 1 row affected (0.06 sec)\n"
"<comment>(If you don't know the order of the columns in the table or want to insert an incomplete record)</comment>\n"
"mysql&gt; <i>INSERT INTO developers (job, name) VALUES('outsourced', 'Jane Doe');</i>\n"
"Query OK, 1 row affected (0.01 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"According to our return result, it appears that the record was inserted\n"
"correctly. What if we want to input more information than just one record?\n"
"That's where the <c>LOAD DATA</c> command comes into play. This loads records\n"
"from a tab separated file. Let's try that by editing a file in our home\n"
"directory with the records. We'll call this file <path>records.txt</path>.\n"
"Here's a sample:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:387
#, no-wrap
msgid "~/records.txt"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:388
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"John Doe\tjohndoe@gentoo.org\tportage\n"
"Chris White\tchriswhite@gentoo.org\tdocumentation\n"
"Sam Smith\tsamsmith@gentoo.org\tamd64\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Be sure you know what data you're dealing with. It's very unsafe to use <c>LOAD\n"
"DATA</c> when you are uncertain of the file's contents!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:399
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now the <c>LOAD DATA</c> command has a somewhat enlongated definition, but\n"
"we'll use the simplest form here.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:403
#, no-wrap
msgid "LOAD DATA Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid "LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE '/path/to/filename' INTO TABLE table;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:408
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<path>/path/to/filename</path> is the directory and filename that will be used.\n"
"table is the name of our table. In this case, our file is\n"
"<path>~/records.txt</path> and the table is developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:413
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading in our data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:414
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE '~/records.txt' INTO TABLE developers;</i>\n"
"Query OK, 3 rows affected (0.00 sec)\n"
"Records: 3  Deleted: 0  Skipped: 0  Warnings: 0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you come up with any strange behaviour, make sure your fields are separated\n"
"by tabs. If you paste information into your infile from another source, it may\n"
"convert your tabs to spaces.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:426
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"That worked well. However, this simply inserts records, and does not give you\n"
"any sort of control over MySQL. Many web applications use sql scripts in order\n"
"to setup MySQL quickly and easily. If you want to use an sql script, you'll\n"
"need to run mysql in batch mode, or source the file. Here's an example of\n"
"running mysql in batch mode:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:433
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL in batch mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:434
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>mysql -u root -h localhost -p &lt; sqlfile</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:438
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Like <c>LOAD DATA</c>, be sure you can tell what <path>sqlfile</path> does.\n"
"<e>Failure to do so may cause your database to be compromised!</e> Another way\n"
"you can accomplish this is to use the <c>source</c> command. This command will\n"
"run mysql commands from an sql file while in the mysql interactive mode. Here\n"
"is how to source an sql file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sourcing an sql file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:446
#, no-wrap
msgid "mysql&gt; <i>source sqlfile;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you see a web application wanting you to run an sql file, the two above\n"
"commands can be used to accomplish that task. We have our table setup, so how\n"
"do we check our fields?  We do this by searching our table with queries.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "Browsing MySQL Tables With Queries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Queries are one of the main features of any SQL database. They help us turn\n"
"data in our tables into something useful. Most queries are done with the\n"
"<c>SELECT</c> command. The <c>SELECT</c> command is fairly complex, and we're\n"
"only going to look at three main forms of the command in this document.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:468
#, no-wrap
msgid "SELECT forms"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:469
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Select all entries in a table)</comment>\n"
"SELECT * FROM table;\n"
"<comment>(Select specific entries in a table)</comment>\n"
"SELECT * FROM table WHERE field=value;\n"
"<comment>(Select specific fields)</comment>\n"
"SELECT field1,field2,field3 FROM table [WHERE field=value];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:478
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Let's take a quick look at the first form. It's relatively simple and gives\n"
"you an overall look of your table. We'll go ahead and run it to see what data\n"
"we have so far.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:483
#, no-wrap
msgid "Contents of our table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:484 en/mysql-howto.xml:680
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SELECT * FROM developers;</i>\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+----------------+\n"
"| name        | email                 | job            |\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+----------------+\n"
"| Joe Smith   | joesmith@gentoo.org   | toolchain      |\n"
"| John Doe    | johndoe@gentoo.org    | portage        |\n"
"| Chris White | chriswhite@gentoo.org | documentation  |\n"
"| Sam Smith   | samsmith@gentoo.org   | amd64          |\n"
"| Jane Doe    | NULL                  | Outsourced job |\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+----------------+\n"
"5 rows in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:498
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We see both the data we inserted through <c>INSERT</c> and those inserted by\n"
"<c>LOAD DATA</c> present. Now, let's say that we just want to see the record\n"
"for Chris White. We can do so with the second form of select as shown below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:503
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting a specific record using SELECT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:504
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SELECT * FROM developers WHERE name = 'Chris White';</i>\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"| name        | email                 | job           |\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"| Chris White | chriswhite@gentoo.org | documentation |\n"
"+-------------+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"1 row in set (0.08 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As expected, the specific entry that we were looking for has been selected. Now,\n"
"let's say we only wanted to know the person's job and email address, not their\n"
"name. We can do so with the third form of <c>SELECT</c> as shown here.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:519
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting a specific record and fields using SELECT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:520
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql> <i>SELECT email,job FROM developers WHERE name = 'Chris White';</i>\n"
"+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"| email                 | job           |\n"
"+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"| chriswhite@gentoo.org | documentation |\n"
"+-----------------------+---------------+\n"
"1 row in set (0.04 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:530
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This method of selection is a lot easier to manage, expecially with larger\n"
"amounts of information, as we'll see later on. Right now, being the root\n"
"mysql user, we have unlimited permissions to do what we wish with the MySQL\n"
"database. In a server environment, a user with such privileges can be quite\n"
"problematic. In order to control who does what with the databases, we setup\n"
"privileges.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:543
#, no-wrap
msgid "MySQL Privileges"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:545
#, no-wrap
msgid "Granting Privileges with GRANT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:549
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Privileges are what kind of access users have to databases, tables, pretty much\n"
"anything. Right now in the gentoo database, the MySQL root account is the only\n"
"account that can access it, given its permissions. Now, let's create two\n"
"somewhat generic users, guest and admin, who will access the gentoo database\n"
"and work with the information in it. The guest account will be a restricted\n"
"one. All it will be able to do is get information from the database, and that's\n"
"it. admin will have the same control as root, but only for the gentoo database\n"
"(not the main mysql databases). Before we start on that, let's have a closer\n"
"look at this somewhat simplified format of the <c>GRANT</c> command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:560
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRANT Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:561
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRANT [privileges] ON database.* TO '[user]'@'[host]' IDENTIFIED BY '[password]';\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:565
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>GRANT</c> is considered to be the way to create a user. Later versions of\n"
"MySQL, however, do contain a <c>CREATE_USER</c> function, though <c>GRANT</c>\n"
"is still preferred.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:571
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First we have the privileges we wish to assign. With what we've learned so far,\n"
"here are some of the privileges you can set:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:576
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>ALL</c> - Gives the all privilege control for the database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:577
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>CREATE</c> - Allows users to create tables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:578
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>SELECT</c> - Allows users to query tables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>INSERT</c> - Allows users to insert data into a table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:580
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>SHOW DATABASES</c> - Allows users to see a list of databases"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:581
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>USAGE</c> - User has no privileges"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>GRANT OPTION</c> - Allows users to grant privileges"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:586
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you're running MySQL to communicate data to a web application, <c>CREATE</c>,\n"
"<c>SELECT</c>, <c>INSERT</c> (discussed here), <c>DELETE</c> and <c>UPDATE</c>\n"
"(for further infomation look up the\n"
"<uri link=\"http://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql/en/grant.html\"> MySQL\n"
"Reference Manual - GRANT and REVOKE Syntax</uri> section) are the only\n"
"permissions you will most likely need. A lot of people make the mistake of\n"
"granting all permissions when it's not really necessary. Check with the\n"
"application developers to see if such permissions will cause issues with\n"
"general operation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:598
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For our admin user, ALL will do. For the guest user, <c>SELECT</c> will be\n"
"sufficient for read only access. database is the database we wish the user\n"
"to have these permissions on. In this example, gentoo is the database. The .*\n"
"means all tables. If you wanted to, you could apply per table access. user is\n"
"the name of the user and host is the hostname the user will be accessing from.\n"
"In most cases, this will be localhost. Finally, password is the user's\n"
"password. Given the information, let's go ahead and create our users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:607
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the admin and guest user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:608
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(admin)</comment>\n"
"mysql&gt; <i>GRANT ALL ON gentoo.* TO 'admin'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';</i>\n"
"<comment>(guest)</comment>\n"
"mysql&gt; <i>GRANT SELECT ON gentoo.* TO 'guest'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:615
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that we have the users setup, let's test them out. First we quit mysql by\n"
"typing <c>quit</c> at the command prompt:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:619
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quitting MySQL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:620
#, no-wrap
msgid "mysql&gt; <i>quit</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:624
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We're now back at the console. Now that we have our users setup, let's go ahead\n"
"and see what they can do.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:631
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing User Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:635
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We shall now attempt to login as the guest user. Currently, the guest user has\n"
"<c>SELECT</c> only privileges. This basically comes down to being able to search\n"
"and nothing more. Go ahead and login with the guest account.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:640
#, no-wrap
msgid "Logging in with the guest account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:641
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>mysql -u guest -h localhost -p</i>\n"
"Enter password:\n"
"Welcome to the MySQL monitor. Commands end with ; or \\g.\n"
"Your MySQL connection id is 6 to server version: 4.0.25\n"
"\n"
"Type 'help;' or '\\h' for help. Type '\\c' to clear the buffer.\n"
"\n"
"mysql&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:652
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now we should test the user restriction(s). Let's switch to the gentoo database:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:655
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switching to the gentoo database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:656
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>USE gentoo;</i>\n"
"Reading table information for completion of table and column names\n"
"You can turn off this feature to get a quicker startup with -A\n"
"\n"
"Database changed\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now let's try to do something we are not supposed to. We'll attempt to create a\n"
"table.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:668
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attempting to create a table with the guest user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:669
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>CREATE TABLE test (test VARCHAR(20), foobar VARCHAR(2));</i>\n"
"ERROR 1044: Access denied for user: 'guest@localhost' to database 'gentoo'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:674
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you can see, this function fails, as our user does not have the appropriate\n"
"access. However, one access we did grant is the <c>SELECT</c> statement. Let's\n"
"go ahead and try that:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:679
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attempting the SELECT statement"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:694
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The command succeeds, and we're given a glimpse of what user permissions can\n"
"do. We did, however, create an admin account as well. This was created to show\n"
"that even all permissions granted users can still have limitations. Go ahead\n"
"and quit MySQL and login as the admin.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:700
#, no-wrap
msgid "Logging in as admin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:701
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>quit</i>\n"
"Bye\n"
"$ <i>mysql -u admin -h localhost -p</i>\n"
"Enter password:\n"
"Welcome to the MySQL monitor. Commands end with ; or \\g.\n"
"Your MySQL connection id is 7 to server version: 4.0.25\n"
"\n"
"Type 'help;' or '\\h' for help. Type '\\c' to clear the buffer.\n"
"\n"
"mysql&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:714
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To begin, we'll try creating a new database with our admin user. This admin\n"
"user will have access similiar to the root MySQL account, and will be able to\n"
"do any kind of modification to the gentoo database it chooses. This will test\n"
"the user's access to the main MySQL database. Remember ealier that we only set\n"
"permissions to a specific database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:721
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attempting to create a new database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:722
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>CREATE DATABASE gentoo2;</i>\n"
"ERROR 1044: Access denied for user: 'admin@localhost' to database 'gentoo2'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:727
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Indeed, the admin user cannot create databases on the main MySQL database,\n"
"despite all his permissions on the gentoo database. However, we're still able\n"
"to use the admin account to modify the gentoo database, as shown here by this\n"
"example data insertion.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:733
#, no-wrap
msgid "Admin permissions in gentoo database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>USE gentoo;</i>\n"
"Reading table information for completion of table and column names\n"
"You can turn off this feature to get a quicker startup with -A\n"
"\n"
"Database changed\n"
"mysql&gt; <i>INSERT INTO developers VALUES('Bob Simmons', 'bobsimmons@gentoo.org', 'python');</i>\n"
"Query OK, 1 row affected (0.08 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:744
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The admin user can access the database as they please. Now sometimes, we need\n"
"to get rid of user permissions. This could be anything from a problematic user\n"
"to a retired employee. Let's take a look at how to disable user permissions\n"
"with the <c>REVOKE</c> command.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:753
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing User Access With The REVOKE Command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:757
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>REVOKE</c> command lets us deny access to a user. We can either deny\n"
"full access, or specific access. In fact, the format is very similiar to\n"
"<c>GRANT</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:762
#, no-wrap
msgid "REVOKE Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:763
#, no-wrap
msgid "REVOKE [privileges] ON database.* FROM '[user]'@'[host]';\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:767
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Options here are explained in the <c>GRANT</c> command section. In this section\n"
"however, we're going to deny full access to a user. Let's say we find out the\n"
"guest account is causing some problems security wise. We decide to revoke all\n"
"privileges. We login as root and do the needful.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:773
#, no-wrap
msgid "Revoking user permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:774
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>REVOKE ALL ON gentoo.* FROM 'guest'@'localhost';</i>\n"
"Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:779
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this case, user access is simple, so per database revoking is not a problem.\n"
"However, in larger cases, you would most likely be using *.* instead of\n"
"gentoo.* to remove user access to all other databases.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:785
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now let's quit and attempt to login as a guest user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:788
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attempting guest user login"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:789
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>mysql -u guest -h localhost -p</i>\n"
"Enter password:\n"
"Welcome to the MySQL monitor. Commands end with ; or \\g.\n"
"Your MySQL connection id is 9 to server version: 4.0.25\n"
"\n"
"Type 'help;' or '\\h' for help. Type '\\c' to clear the buffer.\n"
"\n"
"mysql&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:800
#, no-wrap
msgid "Although we're able to login, our access to gentoo is now gone.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:803
#, no-wrap
msgid "Denied access to guest account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:804
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>USE gentoo;</i>\n"
"ERROR 1044: Access denied for user: 'guest@localhost' to database 'gentoo'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:809
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"And our problematic user is no longer able to access the gentoo database.\n"
"Please note that the user was still able to login. That is because they remain\n"
"in the main MySQL database. Let's take a look at how to completely remove an\n"
"account with <c>DELETE</c> and the MySQL user table.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:818
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing Accounts Using DELETE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:822
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The MySQL user table is a listing of all users and information about them. Make\n"
"sure you're logged in as root. Then go ahead and use the main MySQL database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:826
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the main mysql database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:827
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>USE mysql;</i>\n"
"Reading table information for completion of table and column names\n"
"You can turn off this feature to get a quicker startup with -A\n"
"\n"
"Database changed\n"
"mysql&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:836
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now let's see what tables the mysql database has:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:839
#, no-wrap
msgid "mysql database table listing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:840
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SHOW TABLES;</i>\n"
"+-----------------+\n"
"| Tables_in_mysql |\n"
"+-----------------+\n"
"| columns_priv    |\n"
"| db              |\n"
"| func            |\n"
"| host            |\n"
"| tables_priv     |\n"
"| user            |\n"
"+-----------------+\n"
"6 rows in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:855
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The user table is the table we're after. However, the user table contains 30\n"
"different fields, making it very hard to read. In order to make things easier\n"
"to read, we'll go ahead and use the third version of the <c>SELECT</c>\n"
"statement. The fields we're after are Host and User.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:861
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finding our guest user in the user table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:862
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>SELECT Host,User FROM user WHERE User = 'guest';</i>\n"
"+-----------+-------+\n"
"| Host      | User  |\n"
"+-----------+-------+\n"
"| localhost | guest |\n"
"+-----------+-------+\n"
"1 row in set (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:872
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that we have our information, we can get rid of the guest user.\n"
"This is done with the <c>DELETE</c> command and the syntax is shown below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:876
#, no-wrap
msgid "DELETE Syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:877
#, no-wrap
msgid "DELETE FROM table WHERE field='value';\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:881
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You may notice that <c>DELETE</c> is somewhat similiar to the <c>SELECT</c>\n"
"statement in its format. In this case, the field will be User, and the value\n"
"guest. This will delete the record in the user table where the user is guest,\n"
"successfully deleting our guest user account. Let's go ahead and do that:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:887
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deleting the guest account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:888
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>DELETE FROM user WHERE User='guest';</i>\n"
"Query OK, 1 row affected (0.07 sec)\n"
"<comment>(FLUSH PRIVILEGES is needed to update user permissions)</comment>\n"
"mysql&gt; <i>FLUSH PRIVILEGES;</i>\n"
"Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:896
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It seems to have worked ok. Let's test by logging out and attempting to login\n"
"as our guest user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:900
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attempting login as the guest user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:901
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mysql&gt; <i>quit</i>\n"
"Bye\n"
"$ <i>mysql -u guest -h localhost -p</i>\n"
"Enter password:\n"
"ERROR 1045: Access denied for user: 'guest@localhost' (Using password: YES)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/mysql-howto.xml:909
#, no-wrap
msgid "Our user is now successfully deleted!\n"
msgstr ""

